{
  "texts": [
    "We conduct Leave-One-Out (LOO) ablations on the DeepMath dataset at 1.5B to isolate the contribution of each component in our framework.",
    "As summarized in Table 6, removing any single component-the shared LLM, relativistic critic, critic reasoning, tie option, or replay buffer-results in a significant performance degradation compared to our full method (41.3%).",
    "This uniform drop confirms that all designed mechanisms are essential for the method's overall effectiveness.",
    "Beyond aggregate metrics, we observe distinct failure modes associated with particular missing components, illustrated by the training dynamics.",
    "Necessity of Critic Reasoning."
  ]
}